ann:label: Ebola Virus Disease
ann:description: Expanding on Legrand model to accommodate separate states for Dead and Recovered. Also capturing Safe Burials and Community Burials differently. Most dwell times taken from WHO-ERT_NEJM_2014. Otherwise from Legrand_EpiInf_2002

userInput.ann:label: Infectivity of FuneralCommunity
userInput.ann:description: Infectivity of the deceased while they await burial in the community

userInput.ann:label: Infectivity of Hospital
userInput.ann:description: Infectivity of individuals that are hospitalized

userInput.ann:label: Probability of Infectious to Hospital
userInput.ann:description: Probability or Proportion of infectious individuals that are hospitalized.

userInput.ann:label: Probability of Infectious to FuneralCommunity
userInput.ann:description: Probability or Proportion of individuals that are infectious who die and are buried in the community.

userInput.ann:label: Probability of Infectious to RemovedRecovered
userInput.ann:description: Probability or Proportion of infectious individuals that recover from the disease, without hospitalization

userInput.ann:label: Probability of Hospital to FuneralHospital
userInput.ann:description: Probability or Proportion of hospitalized individuals who die, and are given a *safe and dignified* burial

userInput.ann:label: Probability of Hospital to RemovedRecovered
userInput.ann:description: Probability or Proportion of hospitalized individuals who recover and are discharged from the hospital.
